# Next.js portfolio — always verify by running commands

**Do not end a turn with only “run build yourself” instructions.** Execute the commands here unless the user explicitly asked for a no-terminal conversation.

## After code or config changes

1. **Always run** `npm run build` from the repo root before wrapping up. **Fix** any compile, lint, or type errors and re-run until green.
2. **Also run** `npm run start:local` **in the background** after a successful build when the user is iterating on the site locally or has asked to “run”, “preview”, or “see it”—so **http://127.0.0.1:4783** stays current. If **`EADDRINUSE` / port busy**, use **`npm run start:local:free`** (frees 4783 then starts) instead of stacking duplicate servers.
3. Prefer **`npm run rebuild:serve`** when `.next` may be stale or the user hit chunk/CSS mismatch errors (`clean` → `build` → `start:local`).
4. **Never** run **`npm run dev`** and **`npm run start:local`** at the same time on this repo (shared `.next`).

## Dev vs production

- **`npm run dev`**: use when the user wants HMR / debugging; still run a **`npm run build`** before finishing if you changed `src/` or Next config, unless they only wanted a quick dev check.
- **`start:local`**: production-style preview on port **4783**; default for “show me the site” after edits.
